description: Chris Blackburn I've been lucky enough in my lifetime to attend an OSU vs. Michigan football game, numerous March Madness Games, an NBA final game, a MLB playoff game of my favorite team, and a World Cup soccer match, and yet last night attending the Paralympics Opening Ceremony in Rio was by far my best sporting experience.    I witnessed the definition of courage in Marcia Malsar, one of the torch bearers last night.  Marcia, because of a disease, must use a walking cane to stand and walk.  Last night while carrying the torch, Marcia fell on live TV and in front of thousands at the opening ceremony due to the rain.  Then, as if her legs were that of an ox, and to the roar of the crowd, stood on her own, grabbed the torch, and marched on to the chants of "Never give up."  You need a new  hero in life, look her up.  I witnessed a miracle in front of my own eyes.  Last night's flag bearers were 8 children, all of whom previously could not walk.  However due to special shoes and clothes, were propped by their parents and walked in front of millions to raise the Paralympic flag.  Amazing moment to see and a very emotional moment. Chris Blackburn

description: Chris Blackburn  is with  Tim Bangert  and  3 others . Well, I'm a man of my word.  A few weeks back, I lost a bet to my good friend  Grant Christy  when my Cincinnati Bengals lost to his Buffalo Bills.  As such, this Sunday, December 18, I will be spreading Holiday Joy to drivers in Downtown Hilliard from 1:00 - 2:00 dressed as a holiday moose and dancing to current pop hits and Christmas Classics.  To make this something worth while besides watching a man perform terrible dancing in a moose outfit, I will donate $1 for any honks I receive or $2 for each person that comes and gets their picture with the holiday moose.  The donations will go to Tim Bangert's Let it Grom Team to help fight cancer, Jennifer Kegyes's Hope for HIE Foundation, and Faith Mission to help feed the hungry.  So if you want to help out charity, or just see an idiot dance as a result of poor Bengals football, drive on by between 1:00 - 2:00 this Sunday.  I'll be near the road next to the Hilliard water fountains. Chris Kari Blackburn Hope for HIE Foundation - Hypoxic Ischemic Encephalopathy Kari
